T1  - Swedish business cycles: 1861–1988
AU  - Englund, Peter
AU  - Persson, Torsten
AU  - Svensson, Lars E.O.
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 30
IS  - 3
SP  - 343
EP  - 371
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/12/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(92)90002-J
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329290002J
AB  - We examine Swedish business cycle data for 1861–1988 in the time domain as well as in the frequency domain. There is evidence of a business cycle in the form of considerable spectral mass for cycles between three and eight years. The variability of the series varies considerably over time: for most series it is highest in the inter-war period. Relative variability is fairly stable over time: cross-section ratios between moving standard deviations for the series do not change much. Comovements are also stable over time: correlation coefficients do not change much either.
ER  - 

